conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705195,"age":2,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":0}],"lifeSummary":"When William Filliol was born in 1380, in England, his father, John Filliol, was 29 and his mother, Margaret Walssh, was 35. He married Joan Frome in Husband, Somerset Township, Somerset, Pennsylvania, United States. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died on 22 April 1416, at the age of 36."},"et":{"1380–22 April 1416":"1380–22. aprill 1416","1380–1416":"1380–1416","1386–1434":"1386–1434","1409–1467":"1409–1467","1352–1403":"1352–1403","1345–1383":"1345–1383","12 Mar 1403":"12. märts 1403","1352":"1352","1383":"1383","1382":"1382","1380":"1380","22 April 1416":"22. aprill 1416","about 1409":"umbes 1409","1403":"1403","1467":"1467","1434":"1434","1345":"1345","1386":"1386","1409":"1409","liv1403":"1403","1416":"1416","1ST HUSBAND":"Husband, Somerset Township, Somerset, Pennsylvania, Ameerika Ühendriigid","of Woodlands, Horton, Dorset, England":"Woodlands, Dorset, England","Langton,, England":"Langton, Durham, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"England","Horton, Dorset, England":"Horton, Dorset, England"},"fi":{"1380–22 April 1416":"1380–22. huhtikuuta 1416","1380–1416":"1380–1416","1386–1434":"1386–1434","1409–1467":"1409–1467","1352–1403":"1352–1403","1345–1383":"13